{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πειράω</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.8, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>imperfect</i> <br /><Level1><b>__A </b></Level1> ἐπείρων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.25: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>future</i> -άσω [ᾱ] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 9, 43 \">Refs</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐπείρᾱσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1276, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 517, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.54 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> πεπείρᾱκα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Am.” 26:\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, <i>aorist</i> ἐπειράθην [ᾱ] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.54 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; compare πειράζω. <br /><Level1><b>__B </b></Level1> more frequently in <i>middle</i> <b>πειράομαι</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.193, 24.390, etc.: \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>future</i> -άσομαι [ᾱ] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 959, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Doric dialect</i> <i>2nd pers.</i> <i>plural</i> πειρασεῖσθε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 743, cf. Hippodamus Pythagoreus cited in 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 4.1.94; later πειρᾱθήσομαι “Geoponica” 12.13.12: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> ἐπειρᾱσάμην, <i>Ionic dialect</i> ἐπειρησάμην, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.120, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.135, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.44, +others\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; but <i>aorist</i> <i>passive</i> ἐπειρήθην, <i>Attic dialect</i> ἐπειράθην [ᾱ], found in <i>middle</i> sense, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.384, +others, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.152, +others, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.5 (variant), 33, 6.92, and in later Prose: \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> πεπείρᾱμαι, <i>Ionic dialect</i> -ημαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.23, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 110, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.46, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 584, 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 5.1, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>plural</i> <i>pluperfect</i> ἐπεπείραντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus “fragment” 24.3 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>], <i>Ionic dialect</i> ἐπεπειρέατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.125. (From πεῖρα.) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1> <i>active</i>, <b>attempt, endeavour, try</b>, with <i>infinitive</i>, μήτε τις.. πειράτω διακέρσαι ἐμὸν ἔπος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.8; πειρήσω (δύναμαι) φηλητέων ὄρχαμος εἶναι “hymnus ad Mercurium” 175; π. ἐς τὴν Μηδικὴν ἐσβάλλειν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.84, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1025, +others: followed by ὡς.., 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.66, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.316, etc.; by ὅπως.., 4.545 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>adjective</i> <i>neuter</i>, πολλὰ πειρῶντες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.38; πάντα 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.1122b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i> understood, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.32. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__A.II</b></Level2> with <i>genitive</i> <i>person</i>, <b>make trial of</b> one, μή μευ πειράτω, for the purpose of persuading, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.345, compare 24.433 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of things, τευχέων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 3.1249 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]: in hostile sense, <b>make an attempt on</b>, μήλων πειρήσοντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.301, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.134 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ πειρᾶν τῆς πόλιος, πρὶν.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.82; π. τοῦ χωρίου 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.61; Νισαίας [prev. author] 4.70; ἀλλήλων [prev. author] 7.38; νυμφείας εὐνᾶς 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 5.30. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__A.III</b></Level2> <i>absolutely</i>, ναυσὶ π. <b>make an attempt</b> by sea, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.25; π. ἐπὶ τὴν κώμην [prev. work] 43. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__A.IV</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>experience</b>, τύχης ἐπήρειαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Am.” 46. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.IV.2</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i>, <b>make an attempt on</b> a woman's honour, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 517 (ubiv. Scholia), “Pl.” 150, 1067, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 1.12, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.2.28, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, πειραθεὶς ὁ Ἁρμόδιος ὑπὸ Ἱππάρχου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.54, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 227c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; see below [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus IV, compare πεῖρα 11. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__B</b></Level1> more frequently in <i>middle</i>, with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>try to</b> do, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.5, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.71, 6.138, +others, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 459, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 6.2, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 12.64, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 3.41, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 186b \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>future</i> <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 17.8.4: the \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<i>infinitive</i> is sometimes understood, πειρήσεται (i.e. ἀλύξαι) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.417: followed by εἰ, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.806, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 95b; πειρήσεται αἴ κε θέῃσιν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.601 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; by ἐάν or ἄν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 327, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 638e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; by μὴ.., <b>lest</b>.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.394 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; by ὅπως.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.2.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, frequently in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus, ἐπειρᾶτο ἐπιών 1.77 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; προσβαίνων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 84; π. βιώμενοι 4.139; π. ἀποσχίζων 6.9, compare 5, 50, 7.139, +others\">Refs</a>]; π. σκοπῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 190e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]?? with <i>neuter</i> <i>adjective</i>, τὰ μεγάλα καὶ τὰ μικρὰ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.5.14. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.II</b></Level2> most frequently (V.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus 11) with _genitive_, \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.1</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i> <i>person</i>, <b>make trial of</b> one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.444, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.336, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; νῦν σεῦ, ξεῖνε, ὀΐω πειρήσεσθαι, εἰ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\".. 19.215; ἕο αὐτοῦ ἐν ἔντεσι.. εἰ οἷ ἐφαρμόσσειε 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.384; with _genitive_ not expressed, ἔπεσιν πειρήσομαι 2.73 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἦ πρῶτ᾽ ἐξερέοιτο ἕκαστά τε πειρήσαιτο <b>test</b> him in each particular, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.119 (variant{μυθήσαιτο})\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. θεοῦ <b>make trial of, tempt</b> a god, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.86. γ,compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1663 (troch.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in hostile sense, πρὶν πειρήσαιτ᾽ Ἀχιλῆος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.580 (with _accusative_ _cognate_ added ἀέθλους.. ἐπειρήσαντ᾽ Ὀδυσῆος 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.23): frequently in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus, especially ἀλλήλων πειρᾶσθαι, as ἐπειρῶντο κατὰ τὸ ἰσχυρὸν ἀλλήλων 1.76; πειρᾶσθέ μου γυναικὸς ὡς ἀφράσμονος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1401, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. τῆς Πελοποννήσου <b>make an attempt</b> on it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.100; π. τοῦ τείχους 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.81. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.2</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>make proof</b> or <b>trial of</b>.., σθένεος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.359; ἥβης 23.432 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χειρῶν καὶ σθένεος π., ἢ.. ἦ.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.282 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>try one's chance at</b> or <b>in</b> a work or contest, ἔργου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 18.369 \">Refs</a>]; ἀέθλου, ἀέθλων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.707, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.100, etc.; παλαιμοσύνης [prev. work] 126 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>make proof of, try</b> a weapon, τόξου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 21.159, 180; νευρῆς [prev. work] 410 (but [ὀϊστοί,] τῶν τάχ᾽ ἔμελλον πειρήσεσθαι\">Refs</a>] arrows whose force they were soon <b>to make trial of</b>, i. e.<b>feel</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 418)\">Refs</a>]; also, <b>make proof of, have experience of</b>, especially in <i>perfect</i> <i>passive</i>, first in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus, νηῶν “Op.” 660; οὐ πεπειρημένοι πρότερον [οἱ] Αἰγύπτιοι Ἑλλήνων 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.159, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 118 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πειρασάμενος ἀγαθῶν, δουλείας, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.44, 5.69, compare 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 5.1; κακῶν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.253 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὀρφανίας π., i.e. to be an orphan, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd-2nd c.BC: Phalaris Epistolographus “Epistulae - Epistolographi” 49 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; but π. τινὸς μετρίου <b>find</b> him moderate <b>by experience</b> or <b>on trial</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Aemilius Paulus” 8, compare “Arat.” 43 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; also, πεπείρανται ὅτι.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 27.2. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.3</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>try one's fortune, try the chances of war</b>, αἴ κε θεὸς πειρώμενος ἐνθάδ᾽ ἵκηται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.129 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πειρώμενος ἢ ἐν ἀέθλῳ ἠὲ καὶ ἐν πολέμῳ <b>making trial of one's powers</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 16.590 \">Refs</a>]; Ἕκτορι πειρηθῆναι ἀντιβίην, ἢ.. ἦ.. <b>to try one's fortune</b> against him, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 21.225 \">Refs</a>]; περὶ δ᾽ αὐτῆς πειρηθήτω (i.e. τῆς ἵππου) <b>let</b> him <b>try</b> for her, as a prize, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 23.553. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.III</b></Level2> <b>make a trial</b> or <b>put</b> a matter <b>to the test</b>, ἐν σοὶ πειρώμεθα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 21a: with _dative_ modi, ἐγχείῃ πειρήσομαι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.279 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπειρήσαντο πόδεσσι <b>tried their luck</b> in the foot-race, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.120, compare 205; σφαίρῃ 8.377 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also π. σὺν ἔντεσι, σὺν τεύχεσι π., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.220, 11.386: but in \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i>, οὐδέ τί πω μύθοισι πεπείρημαι I <b>have</b> not <b>tried myself, have</b> not <b>found my skill</b>, in words, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.23: _absolutely_, ὁ πειραθεὶς πιστεύσει 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitum magistro” 1.16 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πεπειραμένος σαφῶς οἶδα <b>by experience</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Hier.” 2.6. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.IV</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i>, <b>make an attempt on</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" (V.A.IV. 2), Διὸς ἄκοιτιν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 2.34. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3987","accentedUnicode":"πειράω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0551","matchingForm":"ἀπείραστος","stepTransliteration":"apeirastos","gloss":"untempted","_zh_tw_Gloss":"不能被試探的","_es_Gloss":"no tentado","_zh_Gloss":"不能被试探的"},{"strongNumber":"G0552","matchingForm":"ἄπειρος","stepTransliteration":"apeiros","gloss":"unacquainted","_zh_tw_Gloss":"沒有經歷","_es_Gloss":"no conocedor","_zh_Gloss":"没有经历"},{"strongNumber":"G1598","matchingForm":"ἐκπειράζω","stepTransliteration":"ekpeirazō","gloss":"to test/tempt","_zh_tw_Gloss":"試探","_es_Gloss":"probar/tentar ","_zh_Gloss":"试探"},{"strongNumber":"G3984","matchingForm":"πεῖρα","stepTransliteration":"peira","gloss":"test","_zh_tw_Gloss":"磨鍊, 試著","_es_Gloss":"prueba","_zh_Gloss":"磨炼, 试着"},{"strongNumber":"G3985G","matchingForm":"πειράζω","stepTransliteration":"peirazō","gloss":"to test/tempt: tempt","_zh_tw_Gloss":"試探","_es_Gloss":"probar/tentar","_zh_Gloss":"试探"},{"strongNumber":"G3985H","matchingForm":"πειράζω","stepTransliteration":"peirazō","gloss":"to test/tempt: test","_zh_tw_Gloss":"試探","_es_Gloss":"probar/tentar","_zh_Gloss":"试探"},{"strongNumber":"G3985I","matchingForm":"πειράζω","stepTransliteration":"peirazō","gloss":"to test/tempt: try","_zh_tw_Gloss":"試探","_es_Gloss":"probar/tentar","_zh_Gloss":"试探"},{"strongNumber":"G3986G","matchingForm":"πειρασμός","stepTransliteration":"peirasmos","gloss":"temptation/testing: temptation","_zh_tw_Gloss":"試探","_es_Gloss":"tentación/prueba","_zh_Gloss":"试探"},{"strongNumber":"G3986H","matchingForm":"πειρασμός","stepTransliteration":"peirasmos","gloss":"temptation/testing: testing","_zh_tw_Gloss":"試探","_es_Gloss":"tentación/prueba","_zh_Gloss":"试探"}],"shortDef":"to try, attempt","mediumDef":"<b>to try, attempt, essay, endeavor,</b> <ref='Act.26.21'>Acts 26:21</ref>*","stepGloss":"to try","stepTransliteration":"peiraō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"intentar","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 嚐試, 企圖 (作某件事) <br>2) 體驗 (來 4:15)","_zh_Definition":"1) 尝试, 企图 (作某件事) <br>2) 体验 (来 4:15)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"thử nghiệm; cố gắng; thử; thử thách; bị cám dỗ. Xem G3984","_zh_tw_Gloss":"想要","_es_Gloss":"tratar de","_zh_Gloss":"想要"}]}